2.5 is a major upgrade: Welcome to AR HyperSquad! 2.5.3 fixes a handful of UI bugs. AR Body Detection With the latest iPhones NOTE: iPhone XR and newer only you can now isolate and apply filters to a person or their background in real time. Point your camera at someone or yourself and tap the glowing Body Recognition button in the top left of the screen. This is an experimental feature that adds much creative potential we can t wait to see what you create! NOTE: Body Recognition currently only works in live capture and runs on these ARKit 3 enabled devices: iPhone XR iPhone XS iPhone XS Max iPhone 11 iPhone 11 Pro iPhone 11 Pro Max and iPad Pro running iOS 13 . Photo to Video You can now instantly turn photos into videos! Try opening a photo from your Camera Roll and simply hold down the capture button to save a video. If you want to create a still photo simply toggle into Still mode. Full HD 4k and above Export For our subscribers imported photos and videos will now export at their native resolutions. That means you can get 4k and above! output from Hyperspektiv! We fixed a limitation in the 2.0 engine that was keeping the max output at 1080p. For our free users you get HD as well! It will be limited to 1080p. 60 FPS Live Capture On newer devices enjoy our complimentary update from 30fps to 60fps. One new free filter: SPECTRUM Two new Premium filters: DOMA and POLLEN. Completely redesigned our graphics engine which should make things run faster and smoother as well as tons of bug fixes.
